title: Ratio of Loans and Discounts to Net Deposits, National Banks for New York, NY
notes:
Monthly Coverage Varies From Year To Year. All Years 1882-1914 Have Scattered Five Month Coverage. Six Months Are Presented For 1915. See Original Series For Makeup Of Loans And Discounts. Net Deposits Subject To Reserve Requirements, Taken Directly From NBER Sheets, Were Checked. Source: Annual Reports Of The Comptroller Of The Currency.

This NBER data series m14051 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
